The paper discusses the implementation of a deep convolutional neural network for image classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of Bayesian optimization and hyperparameters optimization techniques suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of gradient descent and optimization algorithms suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the validation of the architecture with confusion matrix and classification report suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
